# Database Interactions with Drizzle ORM

All database operations must use the Drizzle ORM schema and query patterns defined in `src/db/schema.ts`.

## Required Imports

```typescript
// ✅ GOOD - Always import from schema
import { db } from '@/db';
import { decks, cards, type Deck, type NewDeck, type Card, type NewCard } from '@/db/schema';

// ✅ GOOD - Import Drizzle query helpers
import { eq, desc, asc, and, or } from 'drizzle-orm';
```

## Schema Usage

### ✅ GOOD - Use schema types
```typescript
// Use inferred types from schema
function createDeck(data: NewDeck): Promise<Deck> {
  return db.insert(decks).values(data).returning();
}

function getDeck(id: string): Promise<Deck | undefined> {
  return db.select().from(decks).where(eq(decks.id, id)).get();
}
```

### ❌ BAD - Raw SQL or manual types
```typescript
// DON'T write raw SQL
await db.execute('SELECT * FROM decks WHERE id = $1', [id]);

// DON'T define manual types when schema types exist
interface ManualDeck {
  id: string;
  title: string;
  // ... duplicating schema
}
```

## Query Patterns

### Select Queries
```typescript
// ✅ Single record
const deck = await db.select().from(decks).where(eq(decks.id, id));

// ✅ Multiple records with conditions
const userDecks = await db.select()
  .from(decks)
  .where(eq(decks.userId, userId))
  .orderBy(desc(decks.createdAt));

// ✅ With relations
const deckWithCards = await db.select().from(decks)
  .leftJoin(cards, eq(cards.deckId, decks.id))
  .where(eq(decks.id, id));
```

### Insert Operations
```typescript
// ✅ Single insert
const [newDeck] = await db.insert(decks)
  .values({ title, description, userId })
  .returning();

// ✅ Batch insert
await db.insert(cards).values([
  { deckId, front: 'Question 1', back: 'Answer 1' },
  { deckId, front: 'Question 2', back: 'Answer 2' },
]);
```

### Update Operations
```typescript
// ✅ Update with conditions
await db.update(decks)
  .set({ title: newTitle, updatedAt: new Date() })
  .where(eq(decks.id, id));
```

### Delete Operations
```typescript
// ✅ Conditional delete
await db.delete(cards).where(eq(cards.deckId, deckId));

// ✅ Cascade deletes are handled by schema constraints
await db.delete(decks).where(eq(decks.id, id));
```

## Common Locations

This rule applies everywhere, but database interactions commonly occur in:
- API routes: `src/app/api/**/*.ts`
- Database utilities: `src/db/**/*.ts`
- Server actions: `src/app/**/*actions.ts`
- Library functions: `src/lib/**/*.ts`

## Error Handling

```typescript
// ✅ GOOD - Handle Drizzle errors appropriately
try {
  const deck = await db.select().from(decks).where(eq(decks.id, id));
  if (!deck.length) {
    throw new Error('Deck not found');
  }
  return deck[0];
} catch (error) {
  if (error instanceof Error) {
    throw new Error(`Database error: ${error.message}`);
  }
  throw error;
}
```

## Performance Notes

- Use `.get()` for single record queries when you expect one result
- Use appropriate indexes defined in schema migrations
- Leverage Drizzle's query optimization features
- Use batch operations for multiple inserts/updates